<FIRST>r i PM-Iran-Cities     06-20 0102</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Iran-Cities,0105</SECOND>
<HEAD>Iran Plans to Build New Cities</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran plans to build 12 new cities to house
its soaring population, the official Islamic Republic News Agency
reports.
   The agency, monitored in Nicosia on Monday, quoted Housing
Minister Serajeddin Kazeroni as saying research was needed to
develop construction methods so more people could own homes.
   Kazeroni was quoted as telling the daily newspaper Ettela'at that
cheaper homes should be built that would consume less energy.
   Iran's population has risen over the past decade from 33 to 50
million and is growing at the rate of 2.5 million annually.
</TEXT>
