<FIRST>r i PM-BRF---Chile-Smog     06-20 0123</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF---Chile-Smog,0127</SECOND>
<HEAD>Emergency Plan To Reduce Smog in Santiago</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTIAGO, Chile (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government has ordered a rotating
shutdown of more than 130 factories and banned 50 percent of all
buses from Santiago's streets to reduce smog that has reached
dangerous levels.
   Announcing the emergency measueres on Monday, Transport Minister
Carlos Silva said the use of private and commercial cars in the
capital also will be restricted with one out of five autos barred
from the city streets daily.
   That restriction will be enforced according to the last digit on
the license plates.
   Silva said some 130 Santiago-area factories found to be polluters
will be required to shut down for 24 hours on a rotating basis, 50
factories at a time.
</TEXT>
