<FILEID>AP-NR-06-20-89 0102EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--KhomeiniShrine     06-20 0111</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Khomeini Shrine,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Khomeini Shrine Becoming Center Of New Township</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The burial place of Ayatollah Ruhollah
Khomeini in south Tehran will become one of Islam's largest shrines,
set in parkland and linked with major highways, a local official
says.
   Iran's official Islamic Republic News Agency, monitored in
Nicosia, quoted the district's mayor, Hassan Tayrani, as saying
Monday that 148 acres around Beheshte Zahra cemetery would be
purchased for the complex.
   The highways now being constructed will link the cemetery with
central Tehran, and to Qom, the theological center of Shiite Islam,
where Khomeini, Iran's revolutionary and religious patriarch, taught
for years.
   Khomeini, 86, died June 3.
</TEXT>
