<FIRST>r a PM-PromLawsuit     06-20 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Prom Lawsuit,0189</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lawsuit Over Broken Prom Date Settled Out of Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A high school sophomore who sued a
boy for breaking their prom date wanted an apology but is settling
for $81.28.
   Marlon Shadd, 17, agreed to reimburse Tomontra Mangrum, 15, for
her prom expenses, including shoes and a hairdo, and the costs of
her lawsuit.
   ``It's just stupid,'' Shadd said Monday. ``She's just freaking
out. I don't know what's wrong with her.''
   ``We said we'll pay, just to get rid of it,'' said Shadd's
attorney, Joel Daves III.
   Shadd, who plans to attend Kansas State University on a
basketball scholarship, maintains he called Ms. Mangrum a week
before the prom to say he had hurt his ankle and would not be able
to escort her.
   ``She just didn't believe me,'' Shadd said. ``She thought I was
kidding around.''
   Shadd and Ms. Mangrum have not spoken since the suit was filed,
said Valerie Mangrum, Tomontra's mother.
   ``He has refused to apologize to her, but she felt like the check
was apology enough,'' the mother said.
