<SECOND>PM-BRF--Grease Spill,0124</SECOND>
<HEAD>Truck Flips, Spills Torrent of Burger Grease</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WARREN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Motorists had to plow through a
stomach-turning flood of rancid-smelling burger grease spilled from
an overturned tractor-trailer.
   ``People were pulling over and throwing up,'' Fire Department Lt.
Richard Lessnau said Monday.
   Police closed one block for several hours after 1,200 gallons
spilled from drums when the truck failed to make a turn. The driver
was unhurt.
   ``This stuff just gooshed out of it,'' said Tony Yousif, manager
of a store nearby.
   Rain turned the curb-high flood of grease scraped off restaurant
grills into a smelly soup, officers said. Yousif said one driver
reported parking in his garage, only to have the rotten-meat smell
fill his house.
