<HEAD>President Lauds NBA Champs</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: CORRECTS spelling of Laimbeer in 3rd graf, bgng ``Someone once''</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush paid tribute today to the
National Basketball Association champion Detroit Pistons, saying
their ``brand of bump and run basketball is a winner.''
   In a White House ceremony driven indoors by rain, Bush joked
about the reputation of the Pistons as the ``Bad Boys'' of the NBA.
   ``Someone once said basketball is ballet with a blackboard.
Whoever it was definitely wasn't under the boards with (Bill)
Laimbeer and (Rick) Mahorn. When the shot goes up there I would not
liken that to Swan Lake,'' he said.
   ``But your brand of bump and run basketball is a winner and I
know that your aggressive style has given the Pistons something of a
reputation.''
   But citing their charity work for the Special Olympics, muscular
dystrophy and other causes, Bush said, ``You may be to some the bad
side of basketball, but off the court people see the kinder, gentler
side of the Detroit Pistons.''
   Guard Isiah Thomas and team owner Bill Davidson presented a
basketball to the president.
   Several dozen excited children from the District of Columbia
Police Boys' and Girls' Clubs also got in to see the new NBA champs,
who dethroned the Los Angeles Lakers in a four-game sweep.
