<TEXT>
   The nominations of Adm. James B. Busey to head
the Federal Aviation Administration and Rear Adm. Richard H. Truly
to head the National Aeronautics and Space Administration were sent
to the full Senate Tuesday.
   Both nominations were approved without objection by the Commerce,
Science and Transportation Committee.
   Busey is retiring as commander of U.S. Navy forces in Europe.
