<TEXT>
   A new apartment building collapsed,
killing at least 14 people, authorities said Tuesday.
   The building collapsed Monday night, trapping workers and their
families under debris, police said on condition of anonymity.
   Six people were killed immediately and eight died of injuries,
doctors said. At least 15 people were seriously injured, they said.
   The victims included five members of a family in which only a
2-year-old girl survived.
   Construction on the building was complete, but it had not been
opened to residents, police said. Most of the victims were laborers
and their families asleep on the ground floor, police said.
   Press Trust of India quoted police as saying they were looking
for builders who allegedly supplied sub-standard cement.
   United News of India said two people were arrested but did not
identify them.
