<DOCNO> AP890620-0234 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-20-89 0827EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f PM-InterestRateOptions     06-20 0298</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Interest Rate Options,0307</SECOND>
<HEAD>SEC Okays Interest Rate Options Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Chicago Board Options Exchange says it has
received approval from the Securities and Exchange Commission to
trade options on interest rates and will launch the new products on
Friday.
   Exchange officials say options on interest rates will eliminate
the inverse price-to-rate relationship associated with other
Treasury bond, Treasury bill and Treasury note markets and should
appeal to individual investors.
   ``For the first time, there will be a product based on the level
of interest rates themselves,'' CBOE Chairman Duke Chapman said in a
news release issued Monday.
   An option is a right to buy or sell a financial instrument or
commodity at a specified price by a given date. Investors can use
options to hedge their positions in cash markets or to speculate on
market movements.
   The Chicago Board Options Exchange is the world's largest options
market. The exchange said in it will offer options on both
short-term and long-term interest rates.
   The option on short-term rates will be based on the yield of the
most recently auctioned 13-week Treasury bill. The option on
long-term rates will be based on the average yield-to-maturity of
the two most recently auctioned 7-and 10-year Treasury notes and
30-year Treasury bonds.
   Unlike other interest-rate instruments, the price of these
products is based on a composite that is calculated using
interest-rate yields rather than the prices of bonds or bills.
   The prices of other interest-rate products move in the opposite
direction from the products' yields. But with the new options on
interest rates, prices will move in tandem with interest rates.
   The CBOE also lists options on 201 widely traded stocks, on the
Standard &amp; Poor's 100 and 500 stock indexes and on U.S. Treasury
bonds and notes.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP890620-0235 </DOCNO>
