<FILEID>AP-NR-06-20-89 1330EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-ICI     06-20 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-ICI,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>ICI and Wellcome Sell Animal Health Business To IMC</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Imperial Chemical Industries PLC and Wellcome Group
PLC said Tuesday they agreed to sell their jointly-owned animal
health business to U.S.-owned International Minerals and Chemical
Corp. for $206 million.
   International Minerals and Chemical will also assume $34 million
in debt owed by the division, Coopers Animal Health, the
announcement said.
   ICI and Wellcome announced last December they were negotiating to
sell Coopers. The two companies set up Coopers in 1984 after
deciding to merge their animal health businesses.
   However, ICI and Wellcome subsequently decided Coopers would
perform better as part of a larger animal health care group which
would be better able to cover its research and development costs.
</TEXT>
