<FIRST>r f BC-Diamond-Star     06-20 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Diamond-Star,0173</SECOND>
<HEAD>Diamond-Star Motors Names New Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NORMAL, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lino J. Piedra has been elected chairman of
the board of Diamond-Star Motors Corp., the joint venture of
Chrysler Corp. and Mitsubishi Motors announced Tuesday.
   Piedra, 43, comes to the U.S.-Japanese automaking venture from
Chrysler's International Operations, where he was director of
Renault policy and strategy and coordinated the U.S. automaker's
relationship with Renault.
   Piedra, a native of Cuba, formerly directed Chrysler's office in
Japan and is a member of Mitsubishi's board of directors.
   He replaces G. Glenn Gardner, who returned to Chrysler Motors in
December after overseeing the start of the $650 million factory in
Normal, which produces a two-door sports coupe marketed as the
Mitsubishi Eclipse and the Plymouth Laser.
   Piedra will direct Diamond-Star's 2,600 employees. The plant will
reach full employment of 2,900 workers by July and have an annual
payroll of about $80 million.
   Annual production will be 240,000 cars per year when the assembly
line reaches top speed.
</TEXT>
