<HEAD>Waterford Glass and Unions Agree On Terms, Changes Name</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Waterford Glass Group PLC said Tuesday it has come
to an agreement with its unions that will help restore its
profitability and is changing its name to Waterford Wedgwood PLC.
   The financially troubled Irish maker of fine crystal and Wedgwood
china did not release details of the labor accord.
   Chairman Howard Kilroy told the company's annual meeting that if
the agreement is ``honored and properly managed,'' the company will
be assured of ``a viable long-term future.''
   An audit last year showed that accounting errors were made which
overvalued its inventories by up to $33 million. In the aftermath of
those revelations, Waterford's chairman Paddy Hayes resigned.
