shortly before noon as buying interest waned.
   Airline issues remained active following news Monday that
Northwest Airlines' parent NWA Inc. accepted a $4 billion buyout
offer from a group led by Los Angeles investor Alfred Checchi.
   On the New York Stock Exchange today, NWA fell after soaring on
Monday. Standard &amp; Poor's Corp., a leading credit-rating agency,
said late in the day that a completed purchase by the Checchi group
would likely cause the agency to downgrade its rating of NWA. The
acquisition would increase NWA's total debt from $945 million to
$3.7 billion, second only to Texas Air Corp. among U.S. airlines,
Standard &amp; Poor's said.
