<FIRST>r f BC-PRWire     06-20 0197</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-PR Wire,0204</SECOND>
<HEAD>ABC, PR Newswire, Broadcast Company Announce Joint Venture</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SUNNYVALE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ABC-TV, PR Newswire and the Indesys data
broadcast company announced the formation Tuesday of a joint-venture
wire service to transmit news to entertainment and television
editors and writers throughout the United States and Canada.
   The high-speed wire will feature program changes, production
schedules and the latest news from major broadcast and cable
networks, movie and TV production companies, publishing houses,
record companies, concert tour organizers and other entertainment
sources.
   The system ``will provide news sources with a fast, reliable and
direct link to the entertainment media,'' said David Steinberg,
president of PR Newswire. ``The latest news from New York,
Hollywood, Nashville and overseas will be on editors' desks around
the country within minutes of its release.''
   Information will be transmitted over an FM subcarrier and a
satellite information distribution network to multiple receivers.
   ABC, a subsidiary of Capital Cities-ABC Inc., is the first major
broadcasting network to participate in the wire.
   ``As our business is increasingly affected by new technologies,
we have looked for more efficient and expeditious means to
distribute information about our company,'' said Richard Connelly,
an ABC spokesman.
</TEXT>
