<HEAD>President of Company in Takeover Fight Resigns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TUSTIN, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   MAI Basic Four Inc., which is pursuing a
hostile takeover of Prime Computer Inc., said Tuesday its president
and chief executive officer, William B. Patton Jr., would resign to
pursue personal and business interests.
   Patton, whose resignation takes effect Sunday, will be
temporarily replaced by William Weksel, a member of the board who
previously was president.
   Patton will remain on the board and continue to serve as a
consultant, the company said.
