takeover bid for Natick, Mass.-based Prime in November, said in a
news release that Patton intended to ``devote more time to his other
personal and business interests.''
   MAI Basic is offering $19.50 a share cash for 75 percent of
Prime's stock, plus securities with a face value of $21 a share for
the remaining 25 percent. The cash portion of the bid is worth $975
million. Analysts believe the securities would trade at below face
value.
